review_blob: Full of hops, at first it feels like a double IPA, but then blends into something more balanced.
I havent had a lot of Rauchbier, but I had this at the brewery and bottled and highly recommend both.

The first beer I liked, ever. So it has a special place in my heart. It is tame and drinkable but not boring, a lot like St. Paul. A local beer should fit its surroundings, and this beer does that in my opinion.
